We recommended and Management agreed to:
require the submission of Program of Work (POW) in addition to letter requests from barangays for construction materials to support its procurement;
submit proof of completion or use of construction materials received by the barangay recipients;
prohibit the use of construction materials for private purposes; and
ensure that only barangay officials receive deliveries of construction materials for barangay development.

We recommended and the Municipal Accountant agreed to:
Prepare separate subsidiary ledgers for each road component and LRN Ledger Cards for each local road;
Present in the Notes to Financial Statements the required disclosures pertaining to the road network system;
We also recommended and the Municipal Treasurer agreed to:
In coordination with the other members of the Inventory Committee, prepare and maintain a Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System and the Road Map;
Keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components; and
We further recommended and the Municipal Engineer agreed to:
Provide assistance to the Municipal Accountant and Treasurer in determining the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

We recommended and the Management agreed to:

Designate an area for the storage of delivered supplies/stocks;

The Property Supply Officer to prepare and maintain Stock Cards for each type of supplies/stocks. Additionally, consolidate the approved Requisition and Issue Slips and prepare the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) monthly to be forwarded to the Municipal Accountant as basis for the dropping of the inventory account to expense at a given period;

The Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain Supplies Ledger Card to each of the Inventories accounts to monitor the purchases, issuances and balances at a given period, and to verify the accuracy of valuation of these Inventories accounts in the financial statements; and

The municipality's Inventory Committee to conduct a physical count of all inventories, and prepare and submit the Report of Physical Count of Inventories to the Municipal Accountant for the reconciliation to the accounting records.

We recommended that the Management:

Hire the number of job order personnel that is required for the implementation of infrastructure projects By Administration as provided in the approved Program of Works;

Based the hiring of these job order for the completion of the items of work for the project, and within the duration to complete such works as stated in the approved Program of Work;

Require the Municipal Planning and Development Officer to submit report of those projects with actual labor exceeded the programmed amount to inform the Management, the Municipal Engineer and the Municipal Accountant;

Instruct the Municipal Engineer to prepare Statement of Work Accomplished to support payment of wages of job order personnel together with the Inspection Report and pictures for the implementation of the project. Further, instruct the job orders to fast-track the completion of the on-going projects; and

Strictly observe the provisions of Appendix 1 of the revised IRR of RA No. 9184, and issuances from the COA and CSC on hiring of job order personnel.

We recommended that the Management instruct the Municipal Accountant the following:
Prepare subsidiary ledgers to its Due to NGAs and Due to LGUs account, and reconcile the balances shown in the Statement of Receipts and Disbursements to the accounting records;
Restore the Government Equity account that was adjusted to the Due to NGAs. Then, examine and reconcile available data to present reliable information on its balance in the financial statements;
Record the balance of the LGU counterpart fund as Trust Liabilities, and transfer the unspent balance from the Trust Fund to the General Fund; and
Strictly observe the provisions for keeping of accounts as stated in the Presidential Decree No. 1445 and generally accepted accounting principles.

